HEADWORD: Setaceous
<hw>Se*ta"ceous</hw> <pr>(s⟦esl⟧*t⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>seta</ets> a bristle: cf. F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧tac⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Set with, or
consisting of, bristles; bristly; <as>as, a stiff, <ex>setaceous</ex>
tail</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bristelike in form or texture; <as>as, a
<ex>setaceous</ex> feather; a <ex>setaceous</ex> leaf.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Setback</ent>⟦br⟧
